## 4. Programming assumptions in effect

- **Squat (max focus, current priority phase)**: bias prescribed loads up — athlete consistently lifts heavier than written. Programming format is **flexible, not locked to Texas Method**: pair one volume day (5×5 @ 78-82%) with one heavy-strength day per week (top set in the 85-92% range — heavy 3 / heavy double / occasional single — followed by hypertrophy back-offs). Rotate the heavy-day rep scheme so the stimulus stays fresh.
- **Squat split**: formalized 2x/wk — Mon 5s / Fri 3s by default. Treat 5s and 3s as paired ladders (3RM ~10–15# above current 5RM). When 5s move up, 3s move up the next cycle.
- **Squat-priority phase active**: hinge under-volume accepted. Floor = 1 loaded-hinge session/wk. Reassess at next deload (~5/18-6/01 estimate or earlier if squat stalls).
- **Strict press (max focus, currently parked)**: 1RM at the 155# wall (failed 4/22). Build via accumulated 5×5 volume @ 70-78% (110-120#) plus 1 hypertrophy press accessory (DB OHP 8-10 reps) per press day. No 1RM attempts until earliest 2026-05-18.
- **Training cadence**: 4 days/week, sometimes 5. Do not prescribe 6-day weeks. Optional/flex sessions marked clearly. **Athlete may swap a planned training day with a planned rest day** — design the week so accessory work is portable across days.
- **Thursday is a low-compliance slot** (4/23 partial, 4/30 social rest). Don't put critical lifts (squat, press, bench) or non-negotiable accessory work (RDL hinge floor) on Thursdays.
- **Bench**: protect 1 dedicated bench day per week.
- **Hypertrophy bias on non-priority lifts**: bench, RDL, single-leg, and direct-arm work programmed in the 8-12 rep range (or 5×5 hold, in bench's case until 185# clears). The two priority lifts (squat, press) get the strength stimulus; everything else gets the growth stimulus.
- **Hesitation = bail**: if a rep mid-set hesitates, athlete cuts the set. Frame coach notes accordingly — cut sets are correct reads, not missed PRs.
- **Finisher rotation**: no KB swings two weeks in a row. Cycle modalities.
- **1RM tests**: schedule explicitly on a planned test day with proper warm-up ramp; do not run mid-week impulse attempts.
- **Empty workout file ≠ rest day** — verify by asking before assuming a skip.
- **Z2 / aerobic base** is not in `workout/` (per athlete memory): bike commute, hikes, weekend outdoor cover it. Don't infer absence from logs.
- **No personal identifiers in repo files** — repo is pushed to GitHub. Identifying details stay out.
